cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.GT, cs.SI, cs.DC 

This paper deals with caching popular contents in a heterogeneous cellular network, which is a topic related to network optimization and information theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves optimization problems, which suggests that it could belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of the network, which could place it in the category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
